               Every column of every area has two portions, the calf and                                                                
               the foot.  During preparation of the calf, paragraphs can                   
               be sent to  the foot.  A  column is considered  full when
               the sum of the lines in the calf and the foot exceeds the
               height of the area.

               You can not declare Portion FOOT nor do a RECEIVE for it.
               The compiler automatically declares a FOOT for  each area
               you declare, and does a RECEIVE for it after each line is
               placed in  the calf.  Your  only foothold is  the command
               "SEND FOOT".

               Example:

.COUNT FOOTNOTE INLINE IN PAGE PRINTING "(i)"
.AT "$$" ENTRY "*" $( NEXT FOOTNOTE ; ! ;
.SEND FOOT $( TURN ON "{" PREFACE 1 SPREAD_1 INDENT 0,0
{!} ENTRY
.BREAK )$ )$

